bit to explain the background

00:05:09.010 --> 00:05:12.280
of how things got to there.

00:05:12.280 --> 00:05:16.230
Last October at a colloquium
in Paris sponsored

00:05:16.230 --> 00:05:21.860
by the Turgenev Library Association
where I was invited to speak,

00:05:21.860 --> 00:05:24.990
I recalled 100,000
books and archives

00:05:24.990 --> 00:05:29.400
for the Turgenev Russian Library
in Paris that were plundered

00:05:29.400 --> 00:05:33.000
in the fall of 1940,
shipped off to Germany

00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:39.600
by the Reichsleiter Rosenberg or
ERR as I will refer to it later,

00:05:39.600 --> 00:05:45.180
a special task force initiated
in Paris after the occupation

00:05:45.180 --> 00:05:49.110
by Adolph Hitler's
ideological henchman,

00:05:49.110 --> 00:05:52.540
Reichsleiter Alfred Rosenberg.

00:05:52.540 --> 00:05:59.940
Most of those books from the
BRT, or the Turgenev Library,

00:05:59.940 --> 00:06:04.510
went first to Berlin and then
were evacuated to [foreign words],

00:06:04.510 --> 00:06:08.410
where they ended the war.

00:06:08.410 --> 00:06:14.180
But of those between 6-
and 8000 I've discovered

00:06:14.180 --> 00:06:19.740
and they finally admitted
in the year 2000 are

00:06:19.740 --> 00:06:23.220
in the former Lenin
Library in Moscow,

00:06:23.220 --> 00:06:25.970
which is now the Russian
State Library.

00:06:25.970 --> 00:06:31.870
Another 3- to 4000 I have
discovered were in Minsk.

00:06:31.870 --> 00:06:37.550 position:56%
I wrote many of them in the meantime
were intentionally destroyed

00:06:37.550 --> 00:06:40.610
as unacceptable for
Soviet libraries.

00:06:40.610 --> 00:06:44.440
And others were scattered
throughout the Soviet Union

00:06:44.440 --> 00:06:50.160
because they didn't need all
these Russian books from Paris

00:06:50.160 --> 00:06:53.890
in the Lenin Library because they
were duplicates of things they had.

00:06:53.890 --> 00:06:58.270
And so they used the media
for exchange or sending them

00:06:58.270 --> 00:07:02.010
to libraries as far away as
Hellene [assumed spelling]

00:07:02.010 --> 00:07:05.880
in Ireland, south of Japan.

00:07:05.880 --> 00:07:12.190
But the 3- to 4000, as
I say, are now in Minsk,

00:07:12.190 --> 00:07:15.830
divided between the
National Library of Belaruse

00:07:15.830 --> 00:07:20.420
and the Presidential Library.

00:07:20.420 --> 00:07:25.120
Last year on the anniversary
of, the 70th anniversary

00:07:25.120 --> 00:07:31.200
of the Second World War, only 119
of those books have been returned

00:07:31.200 --> 00:07:37.720
to Paris of -- that is, of the
100,000, returned to Paris.

00:07:37.720 --> 00:07:44.750
And today, to be sure, the Turgenev
Library in Paris is a shadow

00:07:44.750 --> 00:07:50.720
of its pre-war glory as the most
significant Russian library abroad.

00:07:50.720 --> 00:07:58.000
My monograph on the odyssey of the
Turgenev Library tells that story.

00:07:58.000 --> 00:08:02.950
It was published in 2003 by
the International Institute

00:08:02.950 --> 00:08:05.320
of Social History, or IISH,

00:08:05.320 --> 00:08:08.730
in Amsterdam where I've
been Honorary Fellow,

00:08:08.730 --> 00:08:15.510 position:56%
and that's where my archive, Russian
archive database is now housed.

00:08:15.510 --> 00:08:19.090
That institute, together
with its Paris branch,

00:08:19.090 --> 00:08:23.990
suffered the largest non-government
wartime loss of books and archives

00:08:23.990 --> 00:08:27.620
in the Netherlands, many
of which today remain

00:08:27.620 --> 00:08:31.480
in the Russian Federation
and in Belaruse.

00:08:31.480 --> 00:08:34.700
The ERR actually took
over the building

00:08:34.700 --> 00:08:40.240
of the Amsterdam Institute
on the [foreign words].

00:08:40.240 --> 00:08:44.250
My French friend and
colleague, Martine Perla,

00:08:44.250 --> 00:08:48.820
author of the prize-winning study
of French libraries during the war,

00:08:48.820 --> 00:08:55.790 position:56%
estimates that 10 million books were
seized from over 2400 individuals

00:08:55.790 --> 00:09:02.200
and 400 institutions in France
during wartime German occupation.

00:09:02.200 --> 00:09:04.850
A large percentage of
those have never returned

00:09:04.850 --> 00:09:07.520
to their home libraries.

00:09:07.520 --> 00:09:13.530
While across the continent we now
estimate approximately 12 million

00:09:13.530 --> 00:09:18.190
books were transported to the
Soviet Union after the war

00:09:18.190 --> 00:09:24.040
as what they call compensation for
the even more millions of books

00:09:24.040 --> 00:09:29.200 position:56%
that were destroyed and plundered
by the ERR and other German agencies

00:09:29.200 --> 00:09:32.480
in occupied Soviet lands.

00:09:32.480 --> 00:09:38.580
An effort today to try to locate
and account for more of the books

00:09:38.580 --> 00:09:43.840
that were looted during the
war and still displaced --

00:09:43.840 --> 00:09:45.970
I think there are four
points that I would

00:09:45.970 --> 00:09:48.570
like to just emphasize in general.

00:09:48.570 --> 00:09:53.170
First, we need to determine
the German agency responsible

00:09:53.170 --> 00:09:54.690
for the seizure.

00:09:54.690 --> 00:09:59.230
The -- two, the destination
where the books were dispatched,

00:09:59.230 --> 00:10:03.330
and their wartime migration
to the extent that's possible.

00:10:03.330 --> 00:10:06.680
Three, where the books
ended the war.

00:10:06.680 --> 00:10:11.870
And, four, what country
found them after the war?

00:10:11.870 --> 00:10:16.940
Because it's the last two
elements that determine the success

00:10:16.940 --> 00:10:20.440
or failure of post-war restitution.

00:10:20.440 --> 00:10:25.200
Today I emphasize two of
largest concentrations

00:10:25.200 --> 00:10:32.440
of still displaced books looted in
Europe by two rival Nazi agencies,

00:10:32.440 --> 00:10:36.210
one in Minsk and the
second in Prague.

00:10:36.210 --> 00:10:41.420
But let me back up just a few
minutes and tell you a little bit

00:10:41.420 --> 00:10:46.010
about how they got there.

00:10:46.010 --> 00:10:50.990
The ERR that I mentioned
at the outset only operated

00:10:50.990 --> 00:10:56.570
in German-occupied lands
throughout the European continent.

00:10:56.570 --> 00:11:01.320
But their rival was the
Reich Security Main Office,

00:11:01.320 --> 00:11:05.480
[foreign words], whose looted
library collections in Berlin

00:11:05.480 --> 00:11:11.120
by 1943 may well have exceeded
those collected by the ERR.

00:11:11.120 --> 00:11:18.970
Those were books seized by both the
[foreign words] and the Gestapo.

00:11:18.970 --> 00:11:22.470
But, first, let me just
say a word about the ERR.

00:11:22.470 --> 00:11:30.500
I'm currently completing, sponsored
by the Jewish Claims Conference,

00:11:30.500 --> 00:11:35.960
an updated and greatly expanded
ERR archival guide which sort

00:11:35.960 --> 00:11:40.700
of is a continuation of my
archival reference background.

00:11:40.700 --> 00:11:43.170
I think we have this up.

00:11:43.170 --> 00:11:49.380
Covering this volume -- it's
only on the Internet, is --

00:11:49.380 --> 00:11:55.610
covers remaining ERR and related
archival documents in 10 countries

00:11:55.610 --> 00:12:00.310
in 35 repositories as
well as documents hopeful

00:12:00.310 --> 00:12:04.310
in trying to trace the ERR loot.

00:12:04.310 --> 00:12:11.070
In Western Europe, the ERR was
also responsible for seizure

00:12:11.070 --> 00:12:17.550 position:56%
by the [foreign words] which emptied
an estimated 38,000 homes of Jews

00:12:17.550 --> 00:12:21.510
who were deported in Paris alone.

00:12:21.510 --> 00:12:25.280
Or either deported or who had fled.

00:12:25.280 --> 00:12:30.510
My French colleague, Martine
Perla, as a sequel to her book,

00:12:30.510 --> 00:12:34.780
has been posting on a website
thousands of names of individuals

00:12:34.780 --> 00:12:41.300
and institutions whose books
were returned after the war based

00:12:41.300 --> 00:12:43.780
on French library restitution
records

00:12:43.780 --> 00:12:46.610
that have only just
recently been opened.

00:12:46.610 --> 00:12:54.050 position:56%
But in contrast, my point is that
we need to know who took those books

00:12:54.050 --> 00:12:56.710
and where they went, and
why they weren't returned

00:12:56.710 --> 00:12:58.650
and where they might be today.

00:12:58.650 --> 00:13:01.640
And so I've been assisting
the French Committee

00:13:01.640 --> 00:13:09.580
on Jewish Archives pretend a new
website with 10 original ERR lists

00:13:09.580 --> 00:13:14.740
of priority library seizures,
which is also sponsored

00:13:14.740 --> 00:13:19.400
by the Claims Conference
or ERR Project.

00:13:19.400 --> 00:13:23.030
I found those lists in
six different archives

00:13:23.030 --> 00:13:26.910
in five different countries,
the most important being

00:13:26.910 --> 00:13:30.820
in the British Archives,
National Archives [inaudible],

00:13:30.820 --> 00:13:37.010
and surprisingly the most complete
one in the Ukrainian State Archives

00:13:37.010 --> 00:13:40.990
in [foreign word] which is
how I started with the ERR

00:13:40.990 --> 00:13:43.230
because there is the largest batch

00:13:43.230 --> 00:13:48.760
of ERR records remaining
anywhere in the world.

00:13:48.760 --> 00:13:53.950 position:56%
And they're now all online thanks
to the help of the Claims Conference

00:13:53.950 --> 00:13:56.930 position:56%
in a project I've been working with.

00:13:56.930 --> 00:14:01.940
But the -- from these
French lists of the three --

00:14:01.940 --> 00:14:05.520
that are being posted now, three --

00:14:05.520 --> 00:14:08.960
they cover perhaps only
300 library seizures.

00:14:08.960 --> 00:14:12.460
But these are the priority ones.

00:14:12.460 --> 00:14:18.270
And we even have the codes that
the ER used to mark the crates

00:14:18.270 --> 00:14:21.330
that they -- with which
they shipped the books.

00:14:21.330 --> 00:14:23.840
And what's interesting,
as a colleague

00:14:23.840 --> 00:14:28.010 position:56%
at the Holocaust Museum was pointing
out to me with meetings on Monday,

00:14:28.010 --> 00:14:32.400
these are the same codes that they
had for the particular collections

00:14:32.400 --> 00:14:36.100
of art that were seized from
the same prominent French

00:14:36.100 --> 00:14:39.260
Jewish families.

00:14:39.260 --> 00:14:41.530
Why were they seized?

00:14:41.530 --> 00:14:49.230
The ERR had a firm
ideological purpose,

00:14:49.230 --> 00:14:55.440
and I quote from Rosenberg's
own interrogation at Nuremberg

00:14:55.440 --> 00:14:57.610
and his answer, and I quote.

00:14:57.610 --> 00:15:00.470
"To organize with the help
from an [foreign word] composed

00:15:00.470 --> 00:15:04.360
of political leaders and
experts and from the [inaudible]

00:15:04.360 --> 00:15:10.750
of a thorough examination of items
left behind by Jews and Freemasons

00:15:10.750 --> 00:15:15.540
that would provide a basis for
future intellectual study necessary

00:15:15.540 --> 00:15:19.570
for the political, ideological,
and [inaudible] operations

00:15:19.570 --> 00:15:24.120
of both the NSDAP and
the [foreign words]."

00:15:24.120 --> 00:15:27.260
Rosenberg's protected [foreign
words], as he called it,

00:15:27.260 --> 00:15:31.290
was to become the major post-war
university-level training

00:15:31.290 --> 00:15:35.720
and research facility
for the Nazi elite.

00:15:35.720 --> 00:15:38.930
The Central Library of the
[foreign words] was operative

00:15:38.930 --> 00:15:42.930
in Berlin starting early 1959.

00:15:42.930 --> 00:15:47.240
And in 1940, Rosenberg inaugurated
the Institute for Research

00:15:47.240 --> 00:15:52.410
on the Jewish question, or IEJ
as we call it, in Frankfurt.

00:15:52.410 --> 00:15:57.660
The only [foreign words] institute
that was operating during the war

00:15:57.660 --> 00:16:02.640
and the main destination
for Jewish books from Paris.

00:16:02.640 --> 00:16:07.830
And then the seizures spread
to the Netherlands and Belgium,

00:16:07.830 --> 00:16:12.120
and even Greece, the
Baltic countries, in 1941.

00:16:12.120 --> 00:16:16.510
By 1943 IEJ Library
could project a total

00:16:16.510 --> 00:16:21.410
of half a million volumes
from all over Europe.

00:16:21.410 --> 00:16:28.510
And by the time the end of
the war, we could project

00:16:28.510 --> 00:16:32.940
over a million-and-a-half
books and journals that they --

00:16:32.940 --> 00:16:36.740
that ended the war in the
town of [foreign word],

00:16:36.740 --> 00:16:40.010 position:56%
70 kilometers northeast of Frankfurt

00:16:40.010 --> 00:16:44.330
where the IEJ had their
evacuation center.

00:16:44.330 --> 00:16:48.420
However, they'd been forced to
hand over most of the Masonic books

00:16:48.420 --> 00:16:49.720
to the [foreign words],
that were [inaudible]

00:16:49.720 --> 00:16:56.840
because it was Heinrich
Himmler's offices that won

00:16:56.840 --> 00:17:01.760
out for more serious
investigation of the Freemasonry

00:17:01.760 --> 00:17:06.070
and the Masonic quote
enemies of the Reich.

00:17:06.070 --> 00:17:11.040
Berlin was the second major
destination for books seized

00:17:11.040 --> 00:17:13.610
from France and Western Europe.

00:17:13.610 --> 00:17:18.010
And most of the ERR library
operations were there during the

00:17:18.010 --> 00:17:19.870
first years of the war.

00:17:19.870 --> 00:17:22.680
But then the books went in
two different directions.

00:17:22.680 --> 00:17:25.790
Those destined for the Central
Library of the [foreign words]

00:17:25.790 --> 00:17:32.910
or ZBHS went to Austrian Carinthia
to the Monastery of Tanzenberg

00:17:32.910 --> 00:17:36.950
where they ended the
war, about 600,000 books

00:17:36.950 --> 00:17:41.370
for the ZBHS from all over Europe.

00:17:41.370 --> 00:17:45.270
A year before the planned
invasion of Soviet Union,

00:17:45.270 --> 00:17:49.470
ERR also targeted rich East
European immerge holdings in Paris,

00:17:49.470 --> 00:17:53.560
including the Turgenev
Library with which I started

00:17:53.560 --> 00:17:56.290
to serve their purpose of the --

00:17:56.290 --> 00:18:01.000
of research on the
quote "Bolshevik Enemy."

00:18:01.000 --> 00:18:05.930
And they set up an [foreign
words] or Eastern Library of --

00:18:05.930 --> 00:18:09.390
as part of the anti-Bolshevik
research operations

00:18:09.390 --> 00:18:12.030
and its very large
Socialist component

00:18:12.030 --> 00:18:14.980
from my institute in Amsterdam.

00:18:14.980 --> 00:18:20.510 position:56%
They took over the building and all
of the library including the library

00:18:20.510 --> 00:18:24.280
and archives from the Second
