00:56:03.470 --> 00:56:04.770
the French had lists

00:56:04.770 --> 00:56:07.920
in the restitution
records of books returned.

00:56:07.920 --> 00:56:12.550
There were a lot of -- many of
them were from occult [inaudible],

00:56:12.550 --> 00:56:18.640
the ones that the SD had apparently
taken from French collections

00:56:18.640 --> 00:56:22.750
that were about occult sciences.

00:56:22.750 --> 00:56:26.640
This also is a -- and
there was a project in one

00:56:26.640 --> 00:56:28.710
of the other councils
-- I think I really need

00:56:28.710 --> 00:56:32.400 position:56%
to republish this article that I did

00:56:32.400 --> 00:56:36.600
for the Czech conference
with an update now.

00:56:36.600 --> 00:56:40.280
And I am hoping to turn some
of my findings into a book

00:56:40.280 --> 00:56:45.830
about the lost libraries that
will have some of these details

00:56:45.830 --> 00:56:48.860
that have not, simply
not been known.

00:56:48.860 --> 00:56:52.450
But I also think that the
issue at the National Library

00:56:52.450 --> 00:56:55.170
in the Czech Republic
and I think my --

00:56:55.170 --> 00:56:58.220
the Norwegian colleagues
are going to start this.

00:56:58.220 --> 00:57:00.160
I think it's something
that should be brought

00:57:00.160 --> 00:57:02.440
to the attention of [inaudible].

00:57:02.440 --> 00:57:06.680
It's one thing in Minsk
because Belaruse is not a member

00:57:06.680 --> 00:57:07.980
of -- maybe they are a member.

00:57:07.980 --> 00:57:09.980
Probably are a member of IFLA.

00:57:09.980 --> 00:57:13.730
But that's the International
Federation of Library Associations,

00:57:13.730 --> 00:57:17.690
the International [inaudible]
of Library Association.

00:57:17.690 --> 00:57:21.430
And there have been a very
strong movement in IFLA

00:57:21.430 --> 00:57:29.710
about identifying books that
are displaced in foreign --

00:57:29.710 --> 00:57:34.650
I mean particularly the valuable
ones and these autographs.

00:57:34.650 --> 00:57:36.960
And so I think that there may --

00:57:36.960 --> 00:57:39.310
that it should be brought
to the attention.

00:57:39.310 --> 00:57:42.450
And I hope some of the people
here at the National --

00:57:42.450 --> 00:57:48.950
our National Library, the
Library of Congress, will all --

00:57:48.950 --> 00:57:54.750
may also want to take notice
about these types of problems

00:57:54.750 --> 00:58:00.540
because it's a -- they're
talking about major collections,

00:58:00.540 --> 00:58:05.650 position:56%
particularly a more major collection
in Minsk than is the case in Prague.

00:58:05.650 --> 00:58:08.940
I'm afraid that a lot of the
people aren't going to go

00:58:08.940 --> 00:58:11.520
after the witchcraft books.

00:58:11.520 --> 00:58:16.640
I even had a email
last week from a woman

00:58:16.640 --> 00:58:21.520
